subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Male. Body medium sized. Vertex of head divided into conical tubercles. Legs elongate and slender; fore femora about 1.6 times as long as the pronotum, ventrally with 6–15 spines, internal genicular lobe with a small spine, external genicular lobe with 1 elongate movable spur; fore tibiae ventrally with 2–3 external and 1–2 internal spur(s). Mid femora with an elongate movable spur on the internal and genicular lobe, ventrally unarmed; mid tibiae ventrally with 1 external and 1 internal spur. Hind femora beneath with 7–9 inter spines and without outer spines; hind tibiae above with 47–66 outer and inner spines respectively, arrange in groups. Super internal spur of hind tibiae not exceeding the dorso-apical spine of hind metatarsus (
Fig. 1
). Hind metatarsus with bristles beneath. Male epiproct rather short and rounded. Epiphallus of male genitalia triangular (
Figs. 2–3
).

Female. Subgenital plate with hind margin nocthed deeply (
Fig. 4
). Ovipositor longer than half the length of hind femur.
